humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that out of the 12 lymph nodes received, 3 contained metastatic carcinoma. This corresponds to the N2 category in the AJCC staging system, as per New Rule 14. The exact number of positive lymph nodes falls within the range of 4 to 9, which is specified in New Rule 12a. Therefore, the N stage for this patient's cancer is N2.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The N stage is determined by the number of lymph nodes involved and whether there is extracapsular extension. In this report, the patient has 3 positive lymph nodes (out of 12) and extracapsular extension is present. Therefore, the N stage is N2.
